1
00:01:52,905 --> 00:01:54,031
Oh...

2
00:01:54,072 --> 00:01:55,741
You see what happened there?

3
00:01:55,782 --> 00:01:57,659
I'm pretty sure you hit me.

4
00:01:57,701 --> 00:01:59,453
No. I give you left, left.

5
00:01:59,494 --> 00:02:02,039
You think I'll give another
left, and I gave you a right.

6
00:02:04,541 --> 00:02:06,335
I'm just telling you...

7
00:02:06,335 --> 00:02:08,128
that's what boxing's
all about, OK?

8
00:02:08,170 --> 00:02:09,963
You show your opponent
one thing,

9
00:02:09,963 --> 00:02:12,341
and you do
something else.

10
00:02:12,341 --> 00:02:14,843
That's how Ali took
the title from Foreman.

11
00:02:14,843 --> 00:02:17,596
He beat him with a rope-a-dope.
Don't you remember?

12
00:02:17,638 --> 00:02:19,348
I don't remember what day
of the week it is.

13
00:02:22,392 --> 00:02:25,062
That's right. Everyone thought
Ali's arms had run out,

14
00:02:25,103 --> 00:02:27,773
that he's on empty, but he's
just setting Foreman up.

15
00:02:27,814 --> 00:02:29,733
He's letting him
burn himself out.

16
00:02:31,235 --> 00:02:33,278
And then in the eighth round,
he comes.

17
00:02:39,535 --> 00:02:41,286
Poor George
has got nothing left.

18
00:02:42,579 --> 00:02:44,581
I always liked
Bruce Lee movies.

19
00:02:50,379 --> 00:02:51,880
Now you're learning.

20
00:02:56,260 --> 00:02:58,762
Don't look at my hands.
Look at my shoulder.

21
00:02:58,804 --> 00:03:00,722
That's where the punch
is coming from.

22
00:03:00,764 --> 00:03:01,723
See?

23
00:03:06,186 --> 00:03:07,563
You're still
looking at my hands.

24
00:03:07,604 --> 00:03:08,981
Now come on,
let's try it again.

25
00:03:11,358 --> 00:03:13,777
Come on, focus!
Come on! Shoulders, shoulders!

26
00:04:19,510 --> 00:04:22,346
- Here.
- Nah. You keep it.

27
00:04:22,346 --> 00:04:25,641
- Come on, you won.
- Yeah, but I always win.

28
00:04:25,682 --> 00:04:27,809
I mean, I feel
so guilty about it.

29
00:04:27,851 --> 00:04:29,603
Shut up and take it.

30
00:04:36,401 --> 00:04:38,570
You know why you didn't
beat me today, Hale?

31
00:04:38,612 --> 00:04:40,697
You've been boxing
for 20 years...

32
00:04:40,739 --> 00:04:42,783
and you're better at it
than I am?

33
00:04:44,826 --> 00:04:48,163
No. You don't have
the will to win.

34
00:04:49,039 --> 00:04:51,208
Well, your insight
is shattering.

35
00:04:51,250 --> 00:04:52,334
You had me today.

36
00:04:52,417 --> 00:04:55,212
You could have shut me down,
but you blinked.

37
00:04:57,256 --> 00:05:00,092
Yeah, well, we were
only sparring, buddy.

38
00:05:00,884 --> 00:05:03,804
Thinking like that
is exactly why you lost.

39
00:05:03,804 --> 00:05:06,765
- Now take this.
- It's yours.

40
00:05:06,807 --> 00:05:07,850
No, no, no, take it.

41
00:05:07,933 --> 00:05:10,143
If you didn't give it
everything you've got,

42
00:05:10,185 --> 00:05:12,145
then I don't want it.
Go ahead.

43
00:05:12,187 --> 00:05:14,398
You don't understand.
It really is yours.

44
00:05:14,439 --> 00:05:17,192
I took it out of your wallet
while you were in the shower.

45
00:05:34,501 --> 00:05:36,712
- General.
- General.

46
00:05:39,214 --> 00:05:42,301
Major, were you recently
promoted past me?

47
00:05:42,342 --> 00:05:43,177
No, sir.

48
00:05:43,218 --> 00:05:45,846
Then why are you smoking
in my briefing room?

49
00:05:45,888 --> 00:05:49,183
Sorry about that, sir.
That will never happen again.

50
00:05:52,394 --> 00:05:53,437
Sit.

51
00:05:56,481 --> 00:05:58,650
You take off in the Stealth
at 0-dark-30.

52
00:05:58,650 --> 00:06:01,612
Fly a simulated,
low-level border penetration.

53
00:06:02,154 --> 00:06:03,822
Nap of the earth
all the way.

54
00:06:03,822 --> 00:06:07,951
- Scare cows, wake the farmers.
- Not tonight, buddy.

55
00:06:07,993 --> 00:06:10,746
We're flying the B3
with two live nukes.

56
00:06:11,371 --> 00:06:12,831
Palmdale's
concerned about...

57
00:06:12,831 --> 00:06:14,541
low-level gamma
and x-ray diffusion...

58
00:06:14,583 --> 00:06:16,001
screwing up the peripherals.

59
00:06:16,001 --> 00:06:20,297
They want to send up a couple,
see if anything glows.

60
00:06:20,339 --> 00:06:23,634
- 61s?
- Big ones. 83s.

61
00:06:23,675 --> 00:06:26,929
Whoo! Crowd pleasers.

62
00:06:49,910 --> 00:06:53,622
How's your head?
All right. I'll be fine.

63
00:06:53,664 --> 00:06:55,207
I'm sorry about that.

64
00:06:55,249 --> 00:06:57,084
Don't worry.
I'll get you back.

65
00:06:57,125 --> 00:06:59,169
Ah, now you're dreaming.

66
00:06:59,586 --> 00:07:01,046
After you, major.

67
00:07:25,737 --> 00:07:27,906
These exercises
are fantastic.

68
00:07:27,948 --> 00:07:30,117
When we go to war
against Utah,

69
00:07:30,158 --> 00:07:32,286
we are really going
to kick ass.

70
00:07:40,127 --> 00:07:42,212
Ground control,
ready for rollout.

71
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:26,089
Park ranger.

72
00:08:27,049 --> 00:08:29,259
I'd like to speak to you
about this campfire.

73
00:08:29,301 --> 00:08:31,470
Should I go?
No, Wanda. You stay put.

74
00:08:32,554 --> 00:08:36,308
Yeah, I know.
No wood fires in the park.

75
00:08:36,350 --> 00:08:38,644
Wanda has a cold,
and I'm trying to keep her warm.

76
00:08:38,685 --> 00:08:40,646
Sir, have you seen
any other hikers...

77
00:08:40,646 --> 00:08:42,940
or campers
in this area?

78
00:08:42,981 --> 00:08:46,902
Not this time of year.
What's the fine for this?

79
00:08:46,944 --> 00:08:48,153
Pretty steep.

80
00:09:00,123 --> 00:09:01,208
Secured.

81
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:21,854
Jesus Christ.
Drag him out of there.

82
00:09:22,354 --> 00:09:24,606
Be smelling that all night.

83
00:09:33,866 --> 00:09:37,035
Climb heading 287,
flight level 200.

84
00:09:37,077 --> 00:09:39,621
That's 287, 200.

85
00:09:40,747 --> 00:09:42,499
I don't think
that Aurora Project...

86
00:09:42,541 --> 00:09:45,335
is going to happen for me.
Spoke to your buddy Taylor.

87
00:09:45,377 --> 00:09:48,630
He doesn't feel like I have
enough fighter time to qualify.

88
00:09:48,672 --> 00:09:50,048
And what did you
say to him?

89
00:09:50,090 --> 00:09:52,176
Thank you very much,
sir. Good-bye.

90
00:09:52,217 --> 00:09:54,178
You'll never change,
will you?

91
00:09:54,219 --> 00:09:57,306
And that, my friend,
will be your downfall.

92
00:09:57,347 --> 00:10:00,851
- Know what your problem is?
- Yeah. I'm always right.

93
00:10:00,893 --> 00:10:04,188
- You think you're always right.
- That's deep.

94
00:10:04,897 --> 00:10:07,024
You should have made
colonel by now,

95
00:10:07,065 --> 00:10:09,860
but you're too busy pushing
at everybody all the time.

96
00:10:10,235 --> 00:10:13,655
That's an awesome
responsibility, isn't it?

97
00:10:19,578 --> 00:10:21,830
McMurren control,
this is Go-Seven.

98
00:10:22,414 --> 00:10:24,917
Colonel, you boys
in Utah still awake?

99
00:10:24,958 --> 00:10:27,711
Copy, Major Deakins.
We're ready and waiting.

100
00:10:28,086 --> 00:10:29,505
Be advised,
we're going to catch...

101
00:10:29,546 --> 00:10:32,424
your sorry little butts
this morning and bite down hard.

102
00:10:32,424 --> 00:10:34,301
You may pass that
along to Captain Hale...

103
00:10:34,343 --> 00:10:35,886
with my compliments.

104
00:10:35,928 --> 00:10:38,096
Wilkins
is giving us attitude.

105
00:10:38,138 --> 00:10:40,224
You want to take
a turn tonight?

106
00:10:41,099 --> 00:10:43,519
I'll fly in one ear
and out the other.

107
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:44,895
He won't even know
we were there.

108
00:10:44,937 --> 00:10:48,941
Hale says that
if anyone can catch us, you can.

109
00:10:50,067 --> 00:10:51,735
And everyone get a fix.

110
00:10:51,777 --> 00:10:54,029
They're about to
turn out the lights.

111
00:11:07,417 --> 00:11:10,587
- Ready, captain?
- On your command, major.

112
00:11:10,629 --> 00:11:11,880
Go to war.

113
00:11:12,256 --> 00:11:14,299
Initiating stealth mode.

114
00:11:17,803 --> 00:11:20,180
River valley approach.
Here we go.

115
00:11:26,436 --> 00:11:28,063
Colonel, they've gone
to stealth mode.

116
00:11:28,105 --> 00:11:31,108
We lost them on radar.
Anybody still holding?

117
00:11:31,149 --> 00:11:34,152
Got capture
on their heat signature, sir.

118
00:11:34,194 --> 00:11:36,071
- Good.
- They may be running cold,

119
00:11:36,113 --> 00:11:37,990
but the air above
ten-five is colder.

120
00:11:38,031 --> 00:11:39,992
Good man, Frenchy.
I like that.

121
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:42,202
Descend
to 400 feet AGL,

122
00:11:42,244 --> 00:11:44,246
altimeter setting 3001.

123
00:11:44,288 --> 00:11:47,165
Air speed
.7 Mach 3001, 400 feet.

124
00:11:47,165 --> 00:11:50,002
Nap of the earth.
Here we go.

125
00:12:08,562 --> 00:12:10,981
Terry, you been
through the Needles entrance?

126
00:12:11,023 --> 00:12:13,275
No, why?
Mrs. Parker just called.

127
00:12:13,317 --> 00:12:17,154
Oh, God. What is it this time?
Another UFO?

128
00:12:17,196 --> 00:12:18,989
Or did Elvis drop by for dinner?

129
00:12:19,573 --> 00:12:21,992
She didn't mention him
but said a bunch of trucks...

130
00:12:22,034 --> 00:12:23,952
went through the Needles
entrance an hour ago,

131
00:12:23,994 --> 00:12:26,330
and she thought
they looked suspicious.

132
00:12:27,247 --> 00:12:31,418
Clyde, what exactly does
a suspicious truck look like?

133
00:12:31,752 --> 00:12:34,338
I don't know,
and I have no idea.

134
00:12:34,379 --> 00:12:35,839
Me neither.

135
00:12:36,256 --> 00:12:39,718
The thing is, she said
one of the trucks was ours.

136
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:43,055
You're the only one out tonight,
so if it wasn't you...

137
00:12:43,931 --> 00:12:46,683
She was probably
just hallucinating.

138
00:12:46,725 --> 00:12:48,477
Don't worry.
I'll check it out.

139
00:12:58,612 --> 00:13:00,864
Lost them.
Damn.

140
00:13:01,406 --> 00:13:03,075
Come on, keep hunting.
Keep hunting.

141
00:13:04,743 --> 00:13:08,205
We're below their eyes.
Proceed to primary target.

142
00:13:08,914 --> 00:13:10,999
Descending to 200 feet.

143
00:13:11,458 --> 00:13:13,627
Ridge coming up
in 6 seconds.

144
00:13:13,669 --> 00:13:15,295
I got it.

145
00:13:24,346 --> 00:13:26,682
Whoo! Very nicely done.

146
00:13:26,723 --> 00:13:28,767
- Excellent.
- Switching to autopilot.

147
00:13:28,809 --> 00:13:30,727
Almost
as good as me.

148
00:13:30,769 --> 00:13:33,897
I left a few trees behind.
I'll try to do better next time.

149
00:13:33,939 --> 00:13:35,774
You really love
this shit, don't you?

150
00:13:36,275 --> 00:13:38,652
Where else can you fly
a $2 billion plane...

151
00:13:38,694 --> 00:13:41,029
800 miles an hour
100 feet off the ground?

152
00:13:41,029 --> 00:13:43,699
That is a fact.
That is a fact.

153
00:13:45,784 --> 00:13:47,494
You're in for life, huh?

154
00:13:48,120 --> 00:13:49,913
As long as they'll have me.
Aren't you?

155
00:13:49,955 --> 00:13:52,749
Nah, nah.
I don't think so.

156
00:13:53,458 --> 00:13:54,710
I mean, come on.

157
00:13:56,295 --> 00:13:59,882
You said it yourself,
I should be colonel by now.

158
00:13:59,923 --> 00:14:02,634
Instead, idiots like Boone
become general.

159
00:14:02,676 --> 00:14:04,511
Boone is not
such a bad guy.

160
00:14:04,553 --> 00:14:06,513
If he had a thought
go through his head,

161
00:14:06,555 --> 00:14:08,640
it would be the quickest trip
in North America.

162
00:14:10,142 --> 00:14:11,643
Oh, nah.

163
00:14:12,728 --> 00:14:15,105
Flying doesn't mean
what it used to mean to me.

164
00:14:16,565 --> 00:14:19,359
Not the flying.
Carrying the nukes. I know you.

165
00:14:19,401 --> 00:14:22,154
You love having the power of God
at your fingertips.

166
00:14:22,196 --> 00:14:23,989
You get off on it.

167
00:14:38,754 --> 00:14:41,340
Look out your window.
There's something wrong...

168
00:14:41,381 --> 00:14:42,758
with the terrain
following here.

169
00:14:42,758 --> 00:14:45,219
Shouldn't that starboard ridge
be on our port side?

170
00:14:55,521 --> 00:14:56,897
Aah!

171
00:15:13,956 --> 00:15:15,999
Here she comes.

172
00:15:25,634 --> 00:15:26,677
No!

173
00:15:28,637 --> 00:15:31,682
What the hell
are you doing?

174
00:16:02,963 --> 00:16:05,090
Clyde, I'm looking
at half a valley,

175
00:16:05,132 --> 00:16:07,217
and there's nothing going...

176
00:16:10,721 --> 00:16:12,598
Holy shit!

177
00:16:52,221 --> 00:16:53,639
I got them!

178
00:16:57,267 --> 00:16:58,143
McMurren!

179
00:16:58,185 --> 00:17:02,272
This is Deakins! Hale's lost it!
I'm punching out!

180
00:17:29,341 --> 00:17:31,385
Oh, shit!

181
00:17:33,762 --> 00:17:36,181
Get me search and rescue.
We got pilots down.

182
00:17:42,813 --> 00:17:44,565
Plane crashed
18 minutes ago.

183
00:17:44,606 --> 00:17:47,401
The White House chief of staff
is on his way up.

184
00:17:53,574 --> 00:17:57,452
Good morning, gentlemen.
So, do I wake the President?

185
00:17:58,120 --> 00:18:00,205
- Bill.
- Jack.

186
00:18:02,875 --> 00:18:05,085
Well, what have we got?

187
00:18:05,127 --> 00:18:07,296
We're going out with this.

188
00:18:08,046 --> 00:18:09,798
Rick's team prepared it.

189
00:18:11,884 --> 00:18:14,386
"The United States Air Force
regrets to announce...

190
00:18:14,386 --> 00:18:18,015
"that early this morning
a C141 heavy-lift cargo plane...

191
00:18:18,056 --> 00:18:19,725
"went down
over the Utah desert.

192
00:18:19,725 --> 00:18:22,477
"The status of the crew
has yet to be determined...

193
00:18:22,519 --> 00:18:24,146
Yadda yadda yadda. "

194
00:18:24,563 --> 00:18:26,356
That's very nice bullshit, Rick.

195
00:18:26,398 --> 00:18:28,317
- Thank you, sir.
- We'll go with that.

196
00:18:29,109 --> 00:18:30,110
Wait.

197
00:18:32,571 --> 00:18:34,198
We're making a mistake.

198
00:18:36,742 --> 00:18:38,744
Giles...

199
00:18:38,744 --> 00:18:41,747
You have some input
you wish to share with us?

200
00:18:42,247 --> 00:18:43,290
Yes, sir.

201
00:18:48,212 --> 00:18:50,756
"Aviation Week"
has been following...

202
00:18:50,797 --> 00:18:53,217
the development
of the B3 for years.

203
00:18:53,258 --> 00:18:56,720
They have guys camping out
in lawn chairs all night...

204
00:18:56,762 --> 00:18:58,430
out by the Whiteman
perimeter fence,

205
00:18:58,430 --> 00:19:01,308
watching just in case
one of these things take off.

206
00:19:01,308 --> 00:19:04,603
They're going to know
that one took off last night,

207
00:19:04,603 --> 00:19:07,814
and they're going to know...
that it didn't come back.

208
00:19:07,898 --> 00:19:09,358
We put out a press release...

209
00:19:09,399 --> 00:19:12,945
saying a C141 went down in Utah,
they'll put 2 and 2 together.

210
00:19:12,986 --> 00:19:14,696
"Aviation Week"
is going to run a story.

211
00:19:14,738 --> 00:19:17,699
Everyone's going to know
what really happened,

212
00:19:17,699 --> 00:19:20,619
and we're all going
to look extremely stupid.

213
00:19:22,412 --> 00:19:24,623
We're better off
just telling the truth.

214
00:19:24,665 --> 00:19:28,001
The truth?
How'd you get this job?

215
00:19:37,594 --> 00:19:40,889
- Rewrite it... like Giles said.
- Yes, sir.

216
00:19:41,431 --> 00:19:45,853
I want you to go to Utah.
I'll have my C21 standing by.

217
00:19:45,894 --> 00:19:50,274
That was good work in there.
"Guys in lawn chairs... "

218
00:19:50,607 --> 00:19:54,611
I don't know, Giles.
Sometimes you scare me.

219
00:19:55,112 --> 00:19:58,365
Hell, sir...
sometimes I scare myself.

220
00:20:01,952 --> 00:20:05,789
Move! Move! Move!
Come on!

221
00:20:13,547 --> 00:20:15,215
Wallace, over there!

222
00:20:15,257 --> 00:20:17,009
Reed, check over there!

223
00:20:17,050 --> 00:20:18,719
Kelly, check over there!

224
00:20:34,776 --> 00:20:37,654
- See anything?
- Not a goddamn thing!

225
00:20:38,655 --> 00:20:40,991
Colonel, this is Rhodes.

226
00:20:41,033 --> 00:20:42,117
Go, Max.

227
00:20:42,159 --> 00:20:45,412
Aircraft disintegrated.
Negative survivors on site.

228
00:20:45,454 --> 00:20:46,622
Checking payload. Over.

229
00:20:47,414 --> 00:20:49,333
You watch your needles
there, chief.

230
00:20:52,503 --> 00:20:53,795
Over here!

231
00:20:56,298 --> 00:20:58,133
Over here!

232
00:21:10,604 --> 00:21:12,189
Take that end.

233
00:21:28,163 --> 00:21:30,040
The nukes are gone.

234
00:21:39,925 --> 00:21:41,009
Colonel!

235
00:21:43,011 --> 00:21:44,721
We got ourselves
a Broken Arrow.

236
00:21:48,851 --> 00:21:50,727
You find those nukes, chief.

237
00:21:51,186 --> 00:21:52,646
If your Geigers
pick up more rads...

238
00:21:52,688 --> 00:21:55,190
than you get off a toaster,
I want you out of there.

239
00:21:57,776 --> 00:21:59,152
Broken what?

240
00:21:59,194 --> 00:22:04,116
Broken Arrow. It's a class IV
strategic theater emergency.

241
00:22:04,157 --> 00:22:07,119
It's what we call it
when we lose a nuclear weapon.

242
00:22:07,786 --> 00:22:11,081
I don't know what's scarier,
losing nuclear weapons...

243
00:22:11,123 --> 00:22:14,251
or that it happens so often,
there's a term for it.

244
00:22:14,293 --> 00:22:17,754
They've found the wreckage
90 miles outside of McMurren.

245
00:22:17,754 --> 00:22:19,548
No bombs on board.

246
00:22:20,465 --> 00:22:22,217
This is a real nightmare.

247
00:22:23,552 --> 00:22:25,846
We don't know where
the damn things are.

248
00:22:25,846 --> 00:22:27,931
Cappy, put 2 more teams
in the air.

249
00:22:27,973 --> 00:22:30,934
I want Chief Rhodes backed up
to the fullest extent.

250
00:22:37,149 --> 00:22:38,775
Why didn't they go off?

251
00:22:38,817 --> 00:22:40,777
They have to be armed
to detonate.

252
00:22:40,819 --> 00:22:43,739
They're designed
to survive crashes intact.

253
00:22:43,780 --> 00:22:45,866
They could lie
in burning jet fuel...

254
00:22:45,908 --> 00:22:47,826
for 5 hours... no problem.

255
00:22:47,868 --> 00:22:49,703
So, what the hell happened?

256
00:22:50,162 --> 00:22:51,622
In his last transmission,

257
00:22:51,663 --> 00:22:54,291
Major Deakins said
that Captain Hale lost control.

258
00:22:54,291 --> 00:22:57,794
It's possible one of them
may have hit weapons release...

259
00:22:57,836 --> 00:22:59,254
during the confusion.

260
00:23:46,677 --> 00:23:47,886
Deakins.

261
00:24:02,109 --> 00:24:03,694
You won that round.

262
00:24:16,665 --> 00:24:19,418
Sir! Please turn around!

263
00:24:50,824 --> 00:24:53,785
- Who the hell are you?
- Park ranger.

264
00:24:56,955 --> 00:25:00,125
Just put it down,
and I won't have to kill you.

265
00:25:01,293 --> 00:25:04,046
This isn't a standoff.
I've got the gun.

266
00:25:05,964 --> 00:25:07,674
I never keep it loaded.

267
00:25:18,477 --> 00:25:20,229
Thought you said
it wasn't loaded.

268
00:25:21,313 --> 00:25:24,107
I lied.
Now, who the hell are you?

269
00:25:24,149 --> 00:25:26,401
I'm a captain
in the United States Air Force.

270
00:25:26,443 --> 00:25:30,614
Captain, you're under arrest
until we get this sorted out.

271
00:25:30,656 --> 00:25:32,658
Lady, you're missing
the bigger picture here.

272
00:25:32,699 --> 00:25:33,867
Uh!

273
00:25:36,662 --> 00:25:39,790
Hold still.
All right?

274
00:25:39,831 --> 00:25:42,209
I have already had
a hell of a morning, lady.

275
00:25:42,251 --> 00:25:44,044
I can't tell you
what's going on,

276
00:25:44,086 --> 00:25:45,963
but I need your help, OK?

277
00:25:46,004 --> 00:25:48,090
This is a good way
to convince me.

278
00:25:55,514 --> 00:25:57,307
We both know the gun is loaded.

279
00:25:57,349 --> 00:26:00,102
If I wanted to, I could blow
your head off, right?

280
00:26:02,271 --> 00:26:03,480
Yeah.

281
00:26:06,233 --> 00:26:08,026
But I'm not going to.

282
00:26:10,779 --> 00:26:11,947
Come on.

283
00:26:25,419 --> 00:26:27,462
I got a radio in my truck.

284
00:26:31,633 --> 00:26:33,051
It's this way.

285
00:26:50,652 --> 00:26:52,070
Got them!

286
00:27:15,636 --> 00:27:16,762
We got one.

287
00:27:43,497 --> 00:27:44,790
How you doing?

288
00:27:44,831 --> 00:27:48,085
Hey. You guys need
any help?

289
00:27:48,126 --> 00:27:50,128
It's an Air Force
training exercise, sir.

290
00:27:51,004 --> 00:27:53,549
I'll have to
ask you to leave.

291
00:27:53,590 --> 00:27:56,093
Hey, no problem.
We just, uh...

292
00:27:57,344 --> 00:27:58,887
Oh, jeez.

293
00:28:26,790 --> 00:28:28,709
Any sign of Deakins?

294
00:28:30,169 --> 00:28:31,962
Maybe the son of a bitch
is dead.

295
00:28:32,004 --> 00:28:34,590
What
a terrible thing to say.

296
00:28:45,142 --> 00:28:46,435
Get them.

297
00:28:46,476 --> 00:28:49,021
You assured me
everything would go smoothly.

298
00:28:49,062 --> 00:28:51,440
Everything is going smoothly,
I assure you.

299
00:28:51,481 --> 00:28:54,776
Our merchandise is not
where it's supposed to be.

300
00:28:54,818 --> 00:28:56,778
It's right down there,
Mr. Pritchett.

301
00:28:57,821 --> 00:28:59,281
Everything's on schedule.

302
00:29:11,960 --> 00:29:16,423
Sir, we got one intact.
Let's go find the other one.

303
00:29:16,465 --> 00:29:18,634
Move! Let's go!

304
00:29:19,301 --> 00:29:21,094
Care for a Coke
or something?

305
00:29:21,136 --> 00:29:24,097
2 gunships left McMurren
and are headed this way.

306
00:29:24,139 --> 00:29:26,600
- Wonderful!
- Don't worry about them.

307
00:29:26,600 --> 00:29:29,061
I worry. What about
the other pilot?

308
00:29:29,061 --> 00:29:31,396
- We saw him eject.
- Huh.

309
00:29:32,481 --> 00:29:35,776
Captain Hale. I seriously doubt
that he's alive.

310
00:29:36,151 --> 00:29:39,071
I punched him out when we were
scraping the valley floor.

311
00:29:39,112 --> 00:29:41,615
There's a report
that a park ranger called in.

312
00:29:41,657 --> 00:29:44,034
- She saw a pilot come down.
- Really?

313
00:29:48,330 --> 00:29:49,414
Find her.

314
00:29:56,588 --> 00:29:58,131
I got it!

315
00:30:04,012 --> 00:30:05,764
Hello? McMmurren, come in.

316
00:30:05,806 --> 00:30:06,974
Go, Max.

317
00:30:07,516 --> 00:30:10,269
McMurren, come in. Over.

318
00:30:11,019 --> 00:30:12,437
Max, are you there?

319
00:30:12,479 --> 00:30:13,981
McMurren?

320
00:30:14,022 --> 00:30:14,940
Max.

321
00:30:15,899 --> 00:30:18,235
McMurren, come in.

322
00:30:42,134 --> 00:30:43,343
Move!

323
00:30:45,387 --> 00:30:47,181
Going to open the access panels.

324
00:30:47,890 --> 00:30:49,683
Going to drop in
a couple grenades.

325
00:30:49,725 --> 00:30:52,144
It won't go nuclear,
but it will destroy the bomb...

326
00:30:55,147 --> 00:30:57,232
And whoever's
trying to steal it.

327
00:30:57,900 --> 00:30:59,985
I can't let you do that, chief.

328
00:31:01,820 --> 00:31:03,405
And why not?

329
00:31:12,164 --> 00:31:13,540
All clear!

330
00:31:44,863 --> 00:31:47,991
- Where is your truck?
- Just around the bend.

331
00:31:48,867 --> 00:31:51,495
- How did you find me?
- Saw your chute.

332
00:31:52,371 --> 00:31:56,166
Don't step on that!
There. On that black stuff.

333
00:31:56,208 --> 00:31:59,211
It's cryptogammic soil.
Very fragile.

334
00:31:59,253 --> 00:32:02,214
One footprint takes
centuries to repair.

335
00:32:02,256 --> 00:32:04,967
Come on. Jump. Yeah.

336
00:32:05,008 --> 00:32:07,094
Thought it was a mine
or something.

337
00:32:08,512 --> 00:32:11,515
Endangered dirt.
That's a new one.

338
00:32:15,519 --> 00:32:19,606
Colonel Wilkins,
this is Airman Kelly, sir!

339
00:32:19,606 --> 00:32:22,234
- Go.
- Chief Rhodes is dead!

340
00:32:22,276 --> 00:32:23,569
They're all dead!

341
00:32:23,610 --> 00:32:26,989
What the hell happened?
What the hell happened?!

342
00:32:30,701 --> 00:32:34,705
It's the nuke!
It's open! It's wide open!

343
00:32:35,038 --> 00:32:37,457
Kelly, come in!
What happened?

344
00:32:40,043 --> 00:32:44,506
Oh, God! What am I going to do?

345
00:32:47,801 --> 00:32:49,720
Whoo!

346
00:32:51,722 --> 00:32:55,184
Recall search and rescue.
Get me Washington.

347
00:32:55,726 --> 00:32:57,853
I want N.E.S.T.
On this right now.

348
00:32:57,895 --> 00:33:01,440
- You missed your calling, boy.
- Yeah, Deak. I even bought it.

349
00:33:01,481 --> 00:33:03,317
Make sure
you get Hale! Go!

350
00:33:03,317 --> 00:33:05,152
I'd like to remind you...

351
00:33:05,152 --> 00:33:08,280
there's two attack helicopters
headed this way.

352
00:33:08,322 --> 00:33:11,617
Not anymore.
They've just been recalled.

353
00:33:11,658 --> 00:33:12,993
I'll check the perimeter.

354
00:33:12,993 --> 00:33:14,870
That's where they're headed.
They're going over.

355
00:33:14,912 --> 00:33:16,413
Get to work.

356
00:33:22,669 --> 00:33:24,004
You see, Mr. Pritchett...

357
00:33:24,004 --> 00:33:26,798
they believe they've got
an exposed core...

358
00:33:27,508 --> 00:33:29,593
And that changes
things remarkably...

359
00:33:30,344 --> 00:33:32,179
Because you can't send
people out...

360
00:33:32,179 --> 00:33:35,098
to an active radiation area.
That wouldn't be right.

361
00:33:35,098 --> 00:33:37,976
First, you have to
take a picture from a satellite.

362
00:33:38,018 --> 00:33:40,604
That takes an hour and a half
to change orbit.

363
00:33:40,646 --> 00:33:42,356
Then they send in a N.E.S.T.

364
00:33:43,148 --> 00:33:45,484
That's a Nuclear
Emergency Search Team.

365
00:33:46,568 --> 00:33:49,029
Closest one is
about 2 hours from here.

366
00:33:49,071 --> 00:33:53,033
By the time they find us,
we'll be gone. So relax.

367
00:34:01,500 --> 00:34:03,710
Can your radio
get a signal to McMurren?

368
00:34:03,752 --> 00:34:05,295
I'll have Clyde
patch us through.

369
00:34:05,337 --> 00:34:09,341
We can get your people in here.
Then I can go feed my dog.

370
00:34:12,678 --> 00:34:15,097
Clyde, this is Terry.
Do you read me?

371
00:34:37,202 --> 00:34:40,497
Hello? Clyde, this is Terry.
Do you read me?

372
00:35:21,496 --> 00:35:23,332
Why the hell are they
shooting at us?

373
00:35:23,373 --> 00:35:25,459
We don't have time
to discuss it right now.

374
00:35:25,459 --> 00:35:26,919
Come on.

375
00:35:27,711 --> 00:35:29,379
Let's have some fun.

376
00:35:36,887 --> 00:35:38,430
Aah!

377
00:35:46,730 --> 00:35:48,398
- You OK?
- Yeah.

378
00:35:48,440 --> 00:35:50,067
Give me your gun.

379
00:35:56,907 --> 00:35:58,116
Come on.

380
00:36:14,842 --> 00:36:16,218
Come on.

381
00:36:22,516 --> 00:36:25,060
- You have any more bullets?
- Yeah.

382
00:36:28,689 --> 00:36:30,774
We need to get out
of this canyon.

383
00:36:31,692 --> 00:36:33,777
We can get out
up that way.

384
00:36:34,236 --> 00:36:37,447
Now, if I could get
that bastard to hold still.

385
00:36:37,489 --> 00:36:39,867
- I have an idea.
- Wait. I didn't mean...

386
00:36:54,715 --> 00:36:56,258
Oh, shit.

387
00:37:00,846 --> 00:37:02,973
Don't shoot!

388
00:37:03,849 --> 00:37:05,350
Where is he?

389
00:37:05,392 --> 00:37:06,852
I don't know.

390
00:37:29,458 --> 00:37:30,542
No.

391
00:37:45,974 --> 00:37:47,017
Go!

392
00:37:56,818 --> 00:37:58,612
Holy shit!

393
00:38:01,532 --> 00:38:03,575
Novacek must have hit
a canyon wall.

394
00:38:04,493 --> 00:38:06,828
- You think?
- Maybe.

395
00:38:06,870 --> 00:38:08,038
Maybe?

396
00:38:09,331 --> 00:38:11,750
You said you'd planned
this thing carefully.

397
00:38:12,251 --> 00:38:14,419
How are we going to move
those things now?

398
00:38:15,003 --> 00:38:16,797
Use the trucks.

399
00:38:16,839 --> 00:38:20,133
The trucks!
Now, you listen.

400
00:38:20,676 --> 00:38:23,637
I've spent a lot of money
underwriting this,

401
00:38:23,679 --> 00:38:27,683
and frankly, you're beginning
to shake my confidence!

402
00:38:34,189 --> 00:38:37,484
Well... yeah.
Well, I, uh...

403
00:38:37,526 --> 00:38:40,445
I do appreciate the money
that you and your associates...

404
00:38:40,487 --> 00:38:43,574
have invested
in this operation, but, uh...

405
00:38:43,615 --> 00:38:46,618
it is an operation.
It's a military operation,

406
00:38:46,660 --> 00:38:48,412
and you don't know dick
about that.

407
00:38:48,453 --> 00:38:50,747
I have been in the military
for 20 years.

408
00:38:50,789 --> 00:38:53,834
I planned and flew
over 100 missions in the Gulf.

409
00:38:54,209 --> 00:38:56,628
I put these boys together
because they are motivated...

410
00:38:56,628 --> 00:38:59,006
and they are
highly trained, like me.

411
00:38:59,047 --> 00:39:01,925
This is what I do,
and this is battle,

412
00:39:01,967 --> 00:39:04,761
and battle is a highly
fluid situation.

413
00:39:04,803 --> 00:39:07,598
You plan on your contingencies,
and I have.

414
00:39:07,598 --> 00:39:09,641
You keep your initiative,
and I will.

415
00:39:09,683 --> 00:39:11,643
But what you don't do
is share command.

416
00:39:11,685 --> 00:39:13,228
It's never a good idea.

417
00:39:13,854 --> 00:39:15,731
It's still my money.

418
00:39:19,193 --> 00:39:20,527
And if we succeed,

419
00:39:20,569 --> 00:39:22,613
you and your friends
will get a ton of it.

420
00:39:22,613 --> 00:39:23,989
If we're successful?

421
00:39:24,031 --> 00:39:25,324
Look, Mr. Pritchett,

422
00:39:25,365 --> 00:39:28,493
I will deliver the weapons
to the destination,

423
00:39:28,535 --> 00:39:31,622
but I can't depend
and I can't guarantee...

424
00:39:31,663 --> 00:39:33,707
that those assholes
in Washington...

425
00:39:33,749 --> 00:39:35,751
won't do something stupid
like not pay.

426
00:39:36,210 --> 00:39:37,753
What if they don't?

427
00:39:38,212 --> 00:39:40,464
Well, if they don't...

428
00:39:41,381 --> 00:39:43,425
The Southwest will be
a quiet neighborhood

429
00:39:43,467 --> 00:39:45,802
for about 10,000 years.

430
00:39:54,436 --> 00:39:55,395
Wilkins.

431
00:39:55,437 --> 00:39:58,774
Fax me their last transmission.
How much radiation is tracking?

432
00:40:00,526 --> 00:40:02,444
- Fax that to Mr. Prentice.
- Yes, sir.

433
00:40:02,486 --> 00:40:04,279
So far, we're not
picking up any.

434
00:40:04,321 --> 00:40:06,114
That's kind
of strange, isn't it?

435
00:40:07,074 --> 00:40:09,368
I mean, with an exposed core?

436
00:40:09,451 --> 00:40:12,538
The breach may not be
as bad as we thought.

437
00:40:28,428 --> 00:40:31,723
Colonel... what if this
wasn't an accident?

438
00:40:33,267 --> 00:40:34,726
What are you saying, Giles?

439
00:40:34,768 --> 00:40:37,020
In his final transmission
before the crash,

440
00:40:37,062 --> 00:40:39,273
Major Deakins said
Captain Hale lost it.

441
00:40:39,314 --> 00:40:42,651
We all assume that
to mean pilot error...

442
00:40:42,693 --> 00:40:46,029
or equipment failure,
but what if he meant...

443
00:40:46,071 --> 00:40:48,490
Hale intentionally
lost the plane?

444
00:40:48,532 --> 00:40:50,701
But why would he do that?

445
00:40:50,742 --> 00:40:53,287
Two nuclear weapons
would be worth a lot of money.

446
00:40:53,328 --> 00:40:57,249
To who, son? There are easier
ways to buy nuclear weapons.

447
00:40:57,291 --> 00:40:59,084
Go to one of the old
Soviet republics,

448
00:40:59,126 --> 00:41:02,129
they'll fix you up with a couple
for the price of a BMW.

449
00:41:02,171 --> 00:41:07,259
Sir... I meant, how much
would they be worth to us?

450
00:41:07,301 --> 00:41:09,219
How much would we pay
to get them back?

451
00:41:09,261 --> 00:41:10,637
Hold on.

452
00:41:13,724 --> 00:41:17,186
These nukes have codes that
prevent people from using them.

453
00:41:17,227 --> 00:41:18,520
Of course.

454
00:41:18,562 --> 00:41:20,606
And no one knows
these codes, right,

455
00:41:20,647 --> 00:41:22,524
except for the President
and you guys?

456
00:41:22,566 --> 00:41:25,319
Access to the codes
requires the highest security.

457
00:41:25,360 --> 00:41:28,197
Not even the pilots
have these codes, right?

458
00:41:28,739 --> 00:41:30,449
Where is
that N.E.S.T. Team now?

459
00:41:30,991 --> 00:41:32,367
They just took off, sir.

460
00:41:32,409 --> 00:41:34,828
The E.T.A. In Utah
is 96 minutes.

461
00:41:40,918 --> 00:41:43,545
- Correct 10, left.
- 10-4.

462
00:41:54,932 --> 00:41:57,643
- It's OK.
- It's not OK!

463
00:41:57,684 --> 00:42:01,522
I want to know
what's going on right now!

464
00:42:10,739 --> 00:42:14,034
We were carrying nuclear weapons
on our plane last night.

465
00:42:17,246 --> 00:42:19,790
My former commander
is trying to steal them.

466
00:42:22,417 --> 00:42:25,546
- Oh, my God.
- That's why I need your help.

467
00:42:26,588 --> 00:42:30,259
Without the helicopter,
he won't be able to move them.

468
00:42:30,259 --> 00:42:33,887
Deak will have a backup plan.
He'll be prepared for that.

469
00:42:37,432 --> 00:42:40,018
Trucks. He's got trucks.

470
00:42:40,602 --> 00:42:42,896
Last night Clyde radioed me...

471
00:42:42,938 --> 00:42:46,233
that someone came through
the Needles gate with trucks.

472
00:42:46,942 --> 00:42:50,070
He won't take them towards town.
What else is around here?

473
00:42:53,115 --> 00:42:54,700
The river.

474
00:43:05,377 --> 00:43:06,962
Do you mind?

475
00:43:07,713 --> 00:43:09,464
No, I don't mind at all.

476
00:43:11,550 --> 00:43:13,135
Care for one?

477
00:43:33,697 --> 00:43:36,533
- The one in front has the nukes.
- How do you know?

478
00:43:36,575 --> 00:43:39,369
There's only a driver.
They're keeping the weight down.

479
00:43:39,912 --> 00:43:42,873
- Give me your gun again.
- What are you going to do?

480
00:43:45,250 --> 00:43:46,877
I'll think of something.

481
00:43:46,919 --> 00:43:50,005
Wait. We know where they are.

482
00:43:50,005 --> 00:43:51,423
Let's get to a phone
and call for help.

483
00:43:51,423 --> 00:43:53,509
If they make it to the river,
I'll lose them again.

484
00:43:53,509 --> 00:43:55,177
You get to the phone, OK?

485
00:43:56,345 --> 00:43:59,181
- Then I'm going with you.
- No, you're not.

486
00:43:59,223 --> 00:44:00,766
You're going to need help.

487
00:44:00,766 --> 00:44:03,185
I don't have time
to argue with you, OK?

488
00:44:03,227 --> 00:44:05,437
The nuclear weapons are
my responsibility, not yours.

489
00:44:05,479 --> 00:44:07,773
You're a park ranger.
I'm a military officer.

490
00:44:07,814 --> 00:44:09,149
Just go to the phone.

491
00:44:25,249 --> 00:44:27,835
This is a bad idea.

492
00:44:36,468 --> 00:44:37,636
Hi.

493
00:44:38,178 --> 00:44:39,221
Hi.

494
00:44:41,807 --> 00:44:43,100
Hale! Well, goddamn!

495
00:45:01,702 --> 00:45:02,703
Run him down.

496
00:45:04,204 --> 00:45:05,789
Get him!

497
00:45:09,585 --> 00:45:10,711
Get him!

498
00:45:21,054 --> 00:45:22,097
Fuck!

499
00:45:25,559 --> 00:45:28,270
Don't panic.
Bulletproof glass.

500
00:45:30,564 --> 00:45:31,899
You can get out now.

501
00:45:33,150 --> 00:45:35,444
Looks like we got ourselves
a standoff.

502
00:45:36,778 --> 00:45:39,615
- Aah!
- No... we... don't!

503
00:45:46,413 --> 00:45:47,831
Go! Go!

504
00:45:52,920 --> 00:45:54,922
OK... you can come.

505
00:46:01,762 --> 00:46:02,804
Stay down!

506
00:46:05,224 --> 00:46:09,853
Would you mind not shooting
at the thermonuclear weapons?

507
00:46:19,071 --> 00:46:21,323
Where's St. Jude's
hospital from here?

508
00:46:21,907 --> 00:46:23,659
Salt Lake City, I think.

509
00:46:33,585 --> 00:46:35,379
- Shit!
- What?

510
00:46:35,379 --> 00:46:37,130
We're losing gas.

511
00:46:37,589 --> 00:46:39,216
They must have hit the tank.

512
00:46:39,258 --> 00:46:41,677
We need someplace
to hide these things.

513
00:46:42,344 --> 00:46:43,804
I know a place.

514
00:46:50,394 --> 00:46:51,645
Uh!

515
00:47:02,197 --> 00:47:04,283
What the fuck
are you up to, Hale?

516
00:47:14,251 --> 00:47:15,460
Don't even.

517
00:47:21,300 --> 00:47:22,342
Stop!

518
00:47:28,307 --> 00:47:29,808
Aw, fuck!

519
00:47:36,565 --> 00:47:38,483
You learn that
in survival school?

520
00:47:39,067 --> 00:47:43,071
New Jersey.
Trenton, New Jersey.

521
00:48:15,062 --> 00:48:16,605
What is this place?

522
00:48:17,898 --> 00:48:19,358
It used to be a copper mine.

523
00:48:19,399 --> 00:48:21,652
They shut it down
a couple years ago.

524
00:48:23,987 --> 00:48:26,156
Why would they have a new lock?

525
00:48:32,412 --> 00:48:33,956
All right.

526
00:48:36,750 --> 00:48:39,878
Good move, Hale.
I didn't see it coming...

527
00:48:41,588 --> 00:48:44,716
But you're going to pay for it.
Saddle up, boys.

528
00:49:20,043 --> 00:49:23,714
This place has been prepped.
Deak's been here.

529
00:49:25,424 --> 00:49:27,718
What? You think
he's coming back?

530
00:49:27,718 --> 00:49:31,221
That would be my guess.
May not have a lot of time.

531
00:49:32,097 --> 00:49:33,724
What are we going to do?

532
00:49:40,606 --> 00:49:43,192
We'll just take away
his reason for being here.

533
00:49:44,109 --> 00:49:46,153
Want to help me
unload these things?

534
00:49:53,452 --> 00:49:55,078
Where do you think
they're going?

535
00:49:55,120 --> 00:49:57,873
Same place we were...
the only thing on this road.

536
00:50:09,384 --> 00:50:10,802
My God.

537
00:50:17,476 --> 00:50:19,353
Are you sure you know
what you're doing?

538
00:50:19,978 --> 00:50:21,605
When you fly
with nuclear weapons,

539
00:50:21,647 --> 00:50:23,607
you're trained
to retrieve if possible,

540
00:50:23,649 --> 00:50:27,152
disable if necessary,
and destroy if essential.

541
00:50:27,194 --> 00:50:28,654
And what are we doing?

542
00:50:31,490 --> 00:50:32,908
I'm going to disable it.

543
00:50:34,493 --> 00:50:36,787
You have to arm
these things with a code.

544
00:50:36,828 --> 00:50:40,123
If you enter the wrong code
3 times, the nuke goes dead.

545
00:50:40,165 --> 00:50:42,751
All the circuitry
shuts down and shorts out.

546
00:50:43,877 --> 00:50:45,879
Pretty soon
these things will be...

547
00:50:45,921 --> 00:50:47,923
nothing more
than paperweights.

548
00:50:55,180 --> 00:50:56,640
Hale, pick up.

549
00:50:57,391 --> 00:50:58,976
Pick up!

550
00:50:59,685 --> 00:51:03,021
Come on, buddy.
Pick up the phone.

551
00:51:03,063 --> 00:51:05,524
Buddy, huh?
Son of a bitch.

552
00:51:05,566 --> 00:51:08,652
You tried to kill me.
The friendship is over.

553
00:51:08,694 --> 00:51:10,654
That doesn't mean
I don't like you.

554
00:51:10,696 --> 00:51:12,239
Hell, I'm impressed.

555
00:51:12,281 --> 00:51:15,742
I figured you'd have packed up
and walked off by now.

556
00:51:15,784 --> 00:51:18,328
You figured wrong.
Now I got the nukes.

557
00:51:18,370 --> 00:51:21,290
Guess what, Deak.
I'm going to deactivate them.

558
00:51:22,749 --> 00:51:23,792
You hear that?

559
00:51:23,834 --> 00:51:25,377
That's me punching
the wrong codes.

560
00:51:25,419 --> 00:51:28,172
Pretty soon these things
will be absolutely useless.

561
00:51:28,213 --> 00:51:30,757
Might as well turn around
and drive away.

562
00:51:30,799 --> 00:51:33,302
Outstanding, Hale.
That's the spirit.

563
00:51:33,343 --> 00:51:35,429
Damn. I'm totally screwed now.

564
00:51:36,847 --> 00:51:39,433
Unless I thought of that
ahead of time.

565
00:51:44,688 --> 00:51:46,023
What?

566
00:51:47,232 --> 00:51:48,567
You're kidding.

567
00:51:50,110 --> 00:51:54,573
Didn't work, did it?
I used uncoded circuit boards.

568
00:51:54,615 --> 00:51:58,869
You just activated
a nuclear warhead, my friend.

569
00:51:58,911 --> 00:52:02,206
Setting off a nuke in this mine
has been my plan from day one.

570
00:52:02,247 --> 00:52:04,208
Otherwise, some D.C. Civilian...

571
00:52:04,249 --> 00:52:06,210
might say
I haven't got the guts.

572
00:52:08,504 --> 00:52:09,922
Fuck!

573
00:52:12,132 --> 00:52:14,051
He's insane.

574
00:52:14,092 --> 00:52:18,055
I considered bringing you in.
You know why I didn't?

575
00:52:18,096 --> 00:52:22,017
- Because I would have said no?
- Nah. I'd have just killed you.

576
00:52:22,059 --> 00:52:24,686
I was afraid you'd say yes...

577
00:52:24,728 --> 00:52:27,523
because you don't have the balls
to go through with this.

578
00:52:27,564 --> 00:52:28,941
We both know that.

579
00:52:32,194 --> 00:52:34,613
How deep is this mine?

580
00:52:34,655 --> 00:52:37,074
Uh... about 2,000 feet.

581
00:52:39,076 --> 00:52:40,285
That's plenty.

582
00:52:40,327 --> 00:52:42,579
I'm going to be there
in a few minutes.

583
00:52:42,579 --> 00:52:44,790
Get out of there
as soon as you can.

584
00:52:44,831 --> 00:52:47,084
It's your last move, buddy.

585
00:52:47,084 --> 00:52:49,169
I can think of another move.

586
00:52:49,211 --> 00:52:52,047
I'll keep these together.
If one goes off,

587
00:52:52,089 --> 00:52:55,175
the other gets buried
under a billion tons of rock.

588
00:52:55,175 --> 00:52:57,594
How does that sound?

589
00:52:57,636 --> 00:52:59,930
You wouldn't
do something like that.

590
00:52:59,972 --> 00:53:02,683
You sure about that... buddy?

591
00:53:03,517 --> 00:53:06,061
Shit! Fuck!
He's going to do it.

592
00:53:06,103 --> 00:53:07,062
Let's get him.

593
00:53:07,062 --> 00:53:09,898
We've got to be gone
before he gets here.

594
00:53:18,031 --> 00:53:20,158
I can't do this.

595
00:53:20,200 --> 00:53:23,287
Listen, you told me
this is a copper mine, right?

596
00:53:23,328 --> 00:53:24,830
- Right?
- Right.

597
00:53:24,872 --> 00:53:29,334
The blast will fuse this place
into one big solid copper pot.

598
00:53:29,334 --> 00:53:31,587
- But they're coming!
- That's right.

599
00:53:31,628 --> 00:53:34,882
If I don't get these to a safe
level before they get here,

600
00:53:34,923 --> 00:53:36,842
God knows where he'll use them.

601
00:53:48,228 --> 00:53:50,314
Just keep an eye
on the timer, OK?

602
00:54:05,829 --> 00:54:07,206
All right.

603
00:54:53,252 --> 00:54:54,920
What is that noise?

604
00:54:56,922 --> 00:55:00,551
Water. There's an underground
river beneath this place.

605
00:55:00,592 --> 00:55:02,511
Let's get these things unloaded.

606
00:55:30,956 --> 00:55:32,749
I understand, sir.

607
00:55:32,749 --> 00:55:34,918
I'll advise N.E.S.T.
Of the situation.

608
00:55:34,960 --> 00:55:38,297
As soon as the ground is clean,
I'll send in a dozen gunships.

609
00:55:38,338 --> 00:55:40,257
We'll secure the whole area.

610
00:55:40,299 --> 00:55:41,758
Yes, sir.

611
00:55:45,095 --> 00:55:47,431
- Giles Prentice, sir.
- Wilkins.

612
00:55:47,472 --> 00:55:50,100
- Good to meet you finally.
- Likewise, sir.

613
00:55:50,142 --> 00:55:52,519
That was the chairman,
Mr. Prentice.

614
00:55:52,561 --> 00:55:56,064
According to an N.S.A.
Radio intercept, you were right,

615
00:55:56,106 --> 00:55:59,693
but it's Deakins
stealing the nukes, not Hale.

616
00:56:17,794 --> 00:56:19,421
Now what?

617
00:56:19,463 --> 00:56:21,757
We get out of here
before he shows up.

618
00:56:40,526 --> 00:56:42,945
How many times
do I have to say it?

619
00:56:42,986 --> 00:56:45,364
Please don't shoot
the nuclear weapons.

620
00:57:29,199 --> 00:57:31,660
Kelly, we found the nuke.

621
00:57:31,702 --> 00:57:33,829
We're at the end of tunnel "A."

622
00:57:33,871 --> 00:57:36,456
Put the cold one on the
elevator, and we'll be along.

623
00:57:44,506 --> 00:57:46,300
A service tunnel.
Come on.

624
00:57:48,802 --> 00:57:51,305
Make sure Hale
doesn't get back to the bomb.

625
00:57:51,305 --> 00:57:54,349
And, Johnson,
the clock is ticking.

626
00:58:20,834 --> 00:58:23,837
- Where are you taking us?
- Back to the elevator.

627
00:58:23,879 --> 00:58:26,840
These service tunnels
run between the main shafts.

628
00:58:26,882 --> 00:58:29,510
Now... if we take
the next right...

629
00:58:30,344 --> 00:58:31,553
Aah!

630
00:58:44,274 --> 00:58:47,194
Hey, Hale.
Nice move with the nukes.

631
00:58:47,236 --> 00:58:51,114
Shows initiative, determination.
Proud of you!

632
00:58:52,407 --> 00:58:54,660
But I think I gave us
too much time.

633
00:58:54,701 --> 00:58:56,870
30 whole minutes...
I don't know.

634
00:58:56,912 --> 00:58:59,790
Shows a lack of total
commitment, don't you think?

635
00:58:59,831 --> 00:59:01,625
So I took it down to 13.

636
00:59:05,921 --> 00:59:07,381
I'll be right back.

637
01:00:04,104 --> 01:00:05,147
Bitch!

638
01:00:26,293 --> 01:00:28,879
- All set.
- We'll be right along.

639
01:01:25,310 --> 01:01:27,104
Are you OK?

640
01:01:43,787 --> 01:01:46,373
Well, I got to go.

641
01:01:46,415 --> 01:01:48,876
You two have a nice time
down here.

642
01:01:50,627 --> 01:01:54,214
And don't forget to say hi
to Johnson for me...

643
01:01:54,214 --> 01:01:55,924
when you see him.

644
01:01:55,966 --> 01:01:58,552
20 bucks says
you're going to see him first.

645
01:01:59,678 --> 01:02:01,805
- Really?
- Yeah.

646
01:02:01,847 --> 01:02:05,017
You're going to ransom
Salt Lake City, aren't you?

647
01:02:05,058 --> 01:02:06,643
Why do you say that?

648
01:02:06,685 --> 01:02:08,187
St. Jude's hospital.

649
01:02:08,228 --> 01:02:10,647
You'll hide the warheads
in radiology...

650
01:02:10,689 --> 01:02:13,483
so they don't show up
on satellite scans, right?

651
01:02:13,525 --> 01:02:15,444
Huh. Well, I'm impressed.

652
01:02:16,069 --> 01:02:19,114
Thank you.
So, how much you ask for?

653
01:02:19,156 --> 01:02:22,034
Lots. I got a broker
in Stockholm...

654
01:02:22,075 --> 01:02:24,828
that's going to buy me
5% of Volvo.

655
01:02:24,870 --> 01:02:27,915
For the rest of my years,
I'll live off the dividends,

656
01:02:27,956 --> 01:02:31,001
happy in the knowledge
that I'm helping to make...

657
01:02:31,043 --> 01:02:34,421
the safest automobiles
in the world.

658
01:02:34,463 --> 01:02:37,674
So that's what this
is all about? Money?

659
01:02:37,716 --> 01:02:40,219
- Yeah.
- Bullshit.

660
01:02:40,219 --> 01:02:42,471
You tell me why.
Go ahead.

661
01:02:44,097 --> 01:02:45,766
You tell me why.

662
01:02:45,807 --> 01:02:48,602
Because you've been passed over
for promotion so many times,

663
01:02:48,602 --> 01:02:51,230
you want to show the bastards
you're right.

664
01:02:51,271 --> 01:02:53,857
Maybe it's because
everybody's cashing out,

665
01:02:53,857 --> 01:02:55,359
so why the hell not you?

666
01:02:55,400 --> 01:02:59,154
Maybe your mother dropped you on
your head when you were a baby.

667
01:02:59,196 --> 01:03:00,489
Who the hell cares?

668
01:03:00,531 --> 01:03:02,449
There's no difference
between you...

669
01:03:02,491 --> 01:03:05,077
and a guy who
shoots up a schoolyard.

670
01:03:05,118 --> 01:03:07,579
You both got a head
full of bad wiring.

671
01:03:07,579 --> 01:03:10,332
- What was that?
- You're fucked in the head!

672
01:03:12,584 --> 01:03:13,585
Ha!

673
01:03:14,795 --> 01:03:16,421
I pissed him off.

674
01:03:27,349 --> 01:03:29,518
Uh, uh... it's this way.

675
01:03:40,362 --> 01:03:43,949
Hey, hey, hey!
Where the hell's the other one?

676
01:03:43,991 --> 01:03:44,992
Shut up.

677
01:03:52,875 --> 01:03:54,293
Help us. Come on.

678
01:04:10,058 --> 01:04:11,935
Aah...

679
01:04:11,977 --> 01:04:14,521
What
a Mongolian clusterfuck.

680
01:04:14,521 --> 01:04:17,107
Get the goddamn thing in.
Let's get out of here.

681
01:04:19,860 --> 01:04:21,945
That was the only way out.

682
01:04:24,406 --> 01:04:25,824
Oh, man.

683
01:04:27,159 --> 01:04:29,328
That's it, then, isn't it?

684
01:04:48,263 --> 01:04:49,848
You have any family?

685
01:04:52,726 --> 01:04:55,103
No. Just me and Fred.

686
01:04:56,605 --> 01:05:00,400
Fred. Uh, who's Fred?
Your boyfriend?

687
01:05:00,442 --> 01:05:01,735
No. My dog.

688
01:05:05,697 --> 01:05:06,990
The river.

689
01:05:07,032 --> 01:05:09,368
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

690
01:05:09,409 --> 01:05:13,747
They hit it digging a tunnel.

691
01:05:13,789 --> 01:05:15,999
That's why they shut down
the mine.

692
01:05:16,750 --> 01:05:18,252
Come on.

693
01:05:38,981 --> 01:05:41,191
Hang on.
Four minutes to detonation.

694
01:05:41,817 --> 01:05:44,778
You stupid bastard!
We'll all be killed!

695
01:05:44,820 --> 01:05:46,154
We'll be fine, Mr. Pritchett.

696
01:05:46,154 --> 01:05:49,908
Please keep your voice down.
I'm trying to concentrate.

697
01:05:54,454 --> 01:05:55,873
This should be it.

698
01:06:18,478 --> 01:06:20,814
That seam doesn't go anywhere.

699
01:06:20,814 --> 01:06:22,274
Oh...

700
01:06:32,284 --> 01:06:33,911
One o'clock. On the road.

701
01:06:52,930 --> 01:06:55,390
Attention.
We are federal agents.

702
01:06:55,432 --> 01:06:57,851
Stop your vehicle immediately.

703
01:06:57,893 --> 01:07:00,395
Oh, God! Oh, God!

704
01:07:00,437 --> 01:07:04,149
How does that gunship
fit into your grand strategy?

705
01:07:04,191 --> 01:07:06,109
You don't know
what you're doing!

706
01:07:06,151 --> 01:07:09,321
This is out of control!
I must have been...

707
01:07:12,699 --> 01:07:14,785
Hush. Hush.

708
01:07:14,826 --> 01:07:16,703
Stop your vehicle.

709
01:07:16,745 --> 01:07:19,373
I repeat,
stop your vehicle immediately.

710
01:07:30,008 --> 01:07:31,552
We'll get in front of him.

711
01:07:38,559 --> 01:07:41,228
Do not move,
or you will be fired upon.

712
01:07:42,354 --> 01:07:44,022
Ah-ah!

713
01:07:44,064 --> 01:07:45,649
We are federal agents.

714
01:07:45,649 --> 01:07:49,361
Throw down your weapons
and keep your hands in sight.

715
01:08:12,718 --> 01:08:14,303
I just realized something.

716
01:08:14,344 --> 01:08:17,514
I never actually
killed anyone before.

717
01:08:17,556 --> 01:08:20,726
I mean... I dropped
bombs on Baghdad,

718
01:08:20,726 --> 01:08:23,228
but never face-to-face.

719
01:08:24,730 --> 01:08:26,773
I don't know
what the big deal is.

720
01:08:26,815 --> 01:08:27,941
I really don't.

721
01:08:31,612 --> 01:08:34,406
Turn your electronic equipment
off now.

722
01:08:34,448 --> 01:08:35,782
Throw down your weapons.

723
01:09:19,493 --> 01:09:22,663
- We're losing power!
- Oh, my God!

724
01:09:29,044 --> 01:09:31,213
Control, people. Control.

725
01:09:32,297 --> 01:09:34,299
We've gone red!
Trip the relays!

726
01:09:38,136 --> 01:09:39,888
Aah...

727
01:09:49,523 --> 01:09:51,525
I said, goddamn,
what a rush!

728
01:09:55,279 --> 01:09:56,321
Whoo!

729
01:09:56,321 --> 01:09:57,948
Son of a bitch!

730
01:09:57,990 --> 01:10:00,284
Shock wave took down
the damn chopper.

731
01:10:00,325 --> 01:10:02,452
That's E.M. P...
electromagnetic pulse.

732
01:10:02,494 --> 01:10:04,454
Nuclear blast
sends it out for miles.

733
01:10:04,496 --> 01:10:06,582
Everything electronic
shuts down,

734
01:10:06,623 --> 01:10:08,584
including choppers
and radios.

735
01:10:08,625 --> 01:10:11,795
Hell, we just shut down
McMurren's field communications.

736
01:10:11,837 --> 01:10:14,631
That will put a dent
in their response time, huh?

737
01:10:14,673 --> 01:10:17,843
- Deak, you the man!
- I'm the man!

738
01:10:17,885 --> 01:10:20,137
Shouldn't we be evacuating?

739
01:10:20,137 --> 01:10:22,139
We're fine. It was underground.

740
01:10:22,181 --> 01:10:24,099
Colonel Wilkins
to General Creely.

741
01:10:24,141 --> 01:10:25,684
How do you know?

742
01:10:25,726 --> 01:10:27,728
If it had been
a surface detonation,

743
01:10:27,769 --> 01:10:30,063
we'd have felt a different kind
of ground tremor.

744
01:10:30,105 --> 01:10:32,232
We'd also be burned,
blind, and dying.

745
01:10:36,320 --> 01:10:37,529
We're 10 minutes behind.

746
01:10:37,571 --> 01:10:40,866
Mr. Pritchett, would you mind
stepping outside?

747
01:10:52,878 --> 01:10:54,755
It went off underground,
thank God.

748
01:10:54,796 --> 01:10:56,048
What do we do now?

749
01:10:56,965 --> 01:10:59,927
First, we nail a huge
goddamn lid on this thing.

750
01:10:59,968 --> 01:11:03,388
And with all due respect
to your boy Giles...

751
01:11:03,430 --> 01:11:06,850
and his belief that honesty
is the best policy,

752
01:11:06,892 --> 01:11:09,394
from now until
the end of the world,

753
01:11:09,436 --> 01:11:13,398
what happened in Utah today
was an earthquake.

754
01:11:48,725 --> 01:11:50,978
Hey, it's OK.

755
01:11:51,019 --> 01:11:53,021
My God.
We set off a nuclear bomb.

756
01:11:53,021 --> 01:11:54,481
The walls shielded the blast.

757
01:11:54,523 --> 01:11:56,483
None of the radiation
leaked out.

758
01:11:56,525 --> 01:11:58,485
- We're all right.
- Look at my hands.

759
01:11:58,527 --> 01:12:01,822
- Why are they shaking like that?
- Because the water was freezing.

760
01:12:01,822 --> 01:12:05,033
- That's not normal.
- No, it's OK.

761
01:12:05,033 --> 01:12:08,203
We're just cold.
Just need to get warm.

762
01:12:08,245 --> 01:12:10,080
OK? All right?

763
01:12:14,251 --> 01:12:17,171
Hey, look.
See the butterflies there?

764
01:12:17,212 --> 01:12:19,548
If there was radiation,
they wouldn't survive.

765
01:12:19,590 --> 01:12:22,301
Now, would they? No.

766
01:12:25,888 --> 01:12:27,472
All right?

767
01:12:27,514 --> 01:12:29,057
I guess not.

768
01:12:32,519 --> 01:12:35,480
It says so
in the detonation manual,

769
01:12:35,522 --> 01:12:38,692
that if you see butterflies
after detonation,

770
01:12:38,734 --> 01:12:41,528
you're going to be fine. OK?

771
01:12:44,865 --> 01:12:46,450
It doesn't say that.

772
01:12:47,701 --> 01:12:49,661
I promise you, though,
we're fine.

773
01:12:55,542 --> 01:12:58,337
How far downriver
does this path go?

774
01:12:58,378 --> 01:13:00,088
Three or four miles.

775
01:13:00,088 --> 01:13:03,217
We should get to Deakins
before he gets out of here.

776
01:13:18,482 --> 01:13:19,525
Wait.

777
01:13:25,739 --> 01:13:27,824
Looks like there's
just two of them.

778
01:13:30,661 --> 01:13:32,037
There's more coming.

779
01:13:41,255 --> 01:13:44,925
I thought you said Hale
wouldn't be a problem.

780
01:13:44,967 --> 01:13:48,178
He surprised me, too,
but he's dead, so let's go.

781
01:14:40,856 --> 01:14:43,358
- Sink it?
- Steal it.

782
01:14:56,997 --> 01:14:58,916
- Let's move it.
- They're coming.

783
01:14:58,957 --> 01:15:02,002
Get out of the boat.
Get out of the boat!

784
01:15:32,866 --> 01:15:35,077
Well, your friends
in Washington...

785
01:15:35,118 --> 01:15:37,162
should be getting
the package now.

786
01:15:37,204 --> 01:15:42,084
Yep. I'm sure we got their full
and complete attention.

787
01:15:42,125 --> 01:15:44,753
Let's move it.
We're on a tight schedule.

788
01:16:20,455 --> 01:16:23,709
...$250 million by 1400,
Utah time.

789
01:16:23,709 --> 01:16:27,462
This deadline is not negotiable,
and there is no grace period.

790
01:16:27,462 --> 01:16:29,089
The second device is on a timer.

791
01:16:29,131 --> 01:16:31,717
Shortly after you receive this,
the timer will be activated.

792
01:16:31,758 --> 01:16:34,052
At 1401, I will make a call.

793
01:16:34,094 --> 01:16:36,597
If you have complied,
I will stop the timer.

794
01:16:36,638 --> 01:16:38,473
If you have not...

795
01:17:07,002 --> 01:17:09,046
Yes. Yes, sir. I understand.

796
01:17:11,381 --> 01:17:13,509
- Creely.
- Please hold.

797
01:17:15,719 --> 01:17:18,514
The President is asking if we
know where the device is headed.

798
01:17:18,555 --> 01:17:21,266
If Deakins had a plane waiting,
it could be anywhere.

799
01:17:21,308 --> 01:17:23,393
- We just don't know.
- I do.

800
01:17:24,478 --> 01:17:25,687
One moment, sir.

801
01:17:25,729 --> 01:17:28,190
This is Colonel Jamison.
They've found Captain Hale.

802
01:17:28,232 --> 01:17:30,025
He's at Lake Powell.

803
01:17:48,836 --> 01:17:50,879
This is a really bad idea.

804
01:18:27,583 --> 01:18:30,127
- Sir, the prisoner is secure.
- All right, Tom. Good job.

805
01:18:30,169 --> 01:18:32,212
You gentlemen can R.T.B.
I'll take it.

806
01:18:32,254 --> 01:18:34,047
Roger, sir. Returning to base.

807
01:18:34,965 --> 01:18:38,135
They found the raft
on the other side of the lake.

808
01:18:38,177 --> 01:18:41,305
Tracks from a heavy truck
ran out on the paved road.

809
01:18:43,098 --> 01:18:45,058
- What about the girl?
- What about her?

810
01:18:45,767 --> 01:18:48,395
What about her?
She's an innocent victim.

811
01:18:48,437 --> 01:18:49,771
I got her involved.

812
01:18:49,771 --> 01:18:52,691
You're going to hit that truck
with everything you've got.

813
01:18:52,691 --> 01:18:54,651
I don't want her
becoming a casualty.

814
01:18:54,693 --> 01:18:56,612
Maybe giving her up
is OK with you,

815
01:18:56,653 --> 01:18:58,113
but we're military officers.

816
01:18:58,155 --> 01:19:01,575
We took an oath,
one officer to another.

817
01:19:01,617 --> 01:19:03,911
We have a responsibility
to save that woman's life...

818
01:19:03,952 --> 01:19:05,412
and get back the weapon.

819
01:19:06,622 --> 01:19:08,624
I have a responsibility
to follow orders...

820
01:19:08,665 --> 01:19:09,833
and return you to McMurren.

821
01:19:09,875 --> 01:19:12,461
Do you understand
what orders are, captain?

822
01:19:12,503 --> 01:19:15,589
- Yes, sir, I do.
- Good.

823
01:19:21,678 --> 01:19:23,430
Because I'm about to break them.

824
01:19:27,559 --> 01:19:30,979
- Any argument, Mr. Prentice?
- No, sir.

825
01:19:32,648 --> 01:19:36,527
Just for the record,
I'm not entirely a civilian.

826
01:19:36,568 --> 01:19:40,364
I was actually a lieutenant
in the R.O.T.C. At Yale.

827
01:19:43,700 --> 01:19:45,285
Good for you, lieutenant.

828
01:19:49,831 --> 01:19:51,959
- Is the radio still down?
- Afraid so.

829
01:19:52,000 --> 01:19:54,461
Your chopper will be
refueled in two minutes.

830
01:19:55,295 --> 01:19:57,130
I wish I were going with you.

831
01:19:57,172 --> 01:20:00,050
Captain, what exactly
are you looking for?

832
01:20:00,092 --> 01:20:02,719
- Tracks.
- As in railroad tracks?

833
01:20:02,761 --> 01:20:05,347
Yeah. Deak knows you're covering
every inch of asphalt.

834
01:20:05,389 --> 01:20:07,933
I'll bet 20 bucks
that nuke isn't on a truck.

835
01:20:07,975 --> 01:20:11,562
- It's on a train.
- Let me see the map.

836
01:20:11,603 --> 01:20:13,188
Salt Lake is northwest of here.

837
01:20:13,230 --> 01:20:14,982
These tracks curve east
before Salt Lake.

838
01:20:15,023 --> 01:20:16,316
Why would he do that?

839
01:20:16,358 --> 01:20:18,277
I don't think he's going
to Salt Lake.

840
01:20:20,571 --> 01:20:22,322
But that's where
the closest hospital is.

841
01:20:22,364 --> 01:20:23,991
You found the radiology tag.

842
01:20:24,032 --> 01:20:26,285
That's what's bothering me.
I think he planted it...

843
01:20:26,326 --> 01:20:29,580
to make the person that found it
think that's where he's heading.

844
01:20:30,831 --> 01:20:33,458
- He's doing a rope-a-dope.
- He's doing a what?

845
01:20:34,084 --> 01:20:38,380
Rope-a-dope. It's a boxing term.
Ali and Foreman in Zaire.

846
01:20:38,422 --> 01:20:40,382
I know what the rope-a-dope is.
What's your point?

847
01:20:40,424 --> 01:20:44,052
My point is that everything he
shows us says he's heading west.

848
01:20:44,094 --> 01:20:45,596
He's actually heading east.

849
01:20:47,431 --> 01:20:48,515
Denver.

850
01:20:50,767 --> 01:20:53,645
You said you had Salt Lake
sealed up pretty tight.

851
01:20:53,687 --> 01:20:56,481
What's it going to hurt
if we check out Denver?

852
01:21:15,334 --> 01:21:17,961
Shepherd!
Any trouble with the train crew?

853
01:21:18,003 --> 01:21:20,464
Not a bit.
They went like lambs.

854
01:21:20,506 --> 01:21:23,800
Good for them. Let's get
that satellite dish wired in.

855
01:21:23,800 --> 01:21:25,761
- Already done.
- Excellent.

856
01:21:25,802 --> 01:21:29,056
With this remote, you can shut
the bomb down face-to-face...

857
01:21:29,097 --> 01:21:31,308
or dial it in over the link.

858
01:21:31,350 --> 01:21:33,143
All right.
Let's close this deal.

859
01:21:33,185 --> 01:21:35,270
I want to be airborne
in five minutes...

860
01:21:35,270 --> 01:21:36,897
en route to the mountains.

861
01:21:36,939 --> 01:21:39,733
Contact Washington. Tell them
the bomb's on its way to Denver.

862
01:21:39,775 --> 01:21:41,026
Then contact Geneva.

863
01:21:41,026 --> 01:21:43,820
When the money's in place,
I'll shut down that puppy.

864
01:21:44,863 --> 01:21:47,115
Smile, boys.
We're about to retire.

865
01:21:47,115 --> 01:21:49,243
Let's get this bird unwrapped.

866
01:22:21,275 --> 01:22:22,359
Uhh!

867
01:22:24,236 --> 01:22:26,280
We haven't met.
I'm Max.

868
01:22:32,035 --> 01:22:33,412
Uhh!

869
01:22:35,914 --> 01:22:38,667
You probably thought
I was a computer nerd.

870
01:22:38,709 --> 01:22:40,919
Ha ha ha! Wrong.

871
01:22:40,961 --> 01:22:42,796
I was a Navy S.E.A.L., lady.

872
01:22:42,838 --> 01:22:46,466
You should see what I can do
with just my thumb.

873
01:23:40,938 --> 01:23:44,525
You just saved me $3 million.
I owe you one.

874
01:23:44,566 --> 01:23:46,318
Shoot yourself.
We'll call it square.

875
01:23:46,360 --> 01:23:48,111
Whoa. Attitude.

876
01:23:51,532 --> 01:23:54,201
Now, where's
my little buddy Hale?

877
01:23:54,910 --> 01:23:56,370
He left you alone, didn't he?

878
01:23:56,870 --> 01:24:00,290
Oh, that's his speed...
100% pussy.

879
01:24:01,041 --> 01:24:03,168
He's got more guts
than you think.

880
01:24:06,338 --> 01:24:08,966
But would he have enough guts
to eat a bullet...

881
01:24:09,007 --> 01:24:11,593
before he'd help someone
vaporize a whole city?

882
01:24:11,593 --> 01:24:14,888
I think he'd fold, but not you.

883
01:24:14,888 --> 01:24:17,391
I think you've got
more guts than he does.

884
01:24:17,432 --> 01:24:20,143
I think you'd eat a bullet.

885
01:24:25,440 --> 01:24:26,775
Let's find out.

886
01:24:29,778 --> 01:24:31,238
Now, press four.

887
01:24:32,155 --> 01:24:33,282
Ooh.

888
01:24:38,370 --> 01:24:40,706
Ahh, I said push four.

889
01:24:44,376 --> 01:24:45,878
Go ahead.

890
01:24:45,919 --> 01:24:47,379
Push four.

891
01:24:53,468 --> 01:24:54,970
Ahh.

892
01:24:56,221 --> 01:24:57,306
Four.

893
01:24:59,516 --> 01:25:00,726
Eight.

894
01:25:03,979 --> 01:25:05,147
Seven.

895
01:25:07,232 --> 01:25:08,233
Go ahead.

896
01:25:08,275 --> 01:25:09,401
Please.

897
01:25:09,443 --> 01:25:10,569
Seven.

898
01:25:15,157 --> 01:25:16,700
Starting at ground zero...

899
01:25:16,742 --> 01:25:18,744
and moving out
in concentric circles,

900
01:25:18,785 --> 01:25:20,662
we have, in terms
of immediate effect,

901
01:25:20,662 --> 01:25:24,750
100% fatalities to 30 miles,
90% at 40 miles,

902
01:25:24,791 --> 01:25:28,212
dropping roughly 10%
for every 10 miles after that.

903
01:25:28,837 --> 01:25:29,880
Two.

904
01:25:32,508 --> 01:25:33,675
One.

905
01:25:37,012 --> 01:25:38,305
Enter.

906
01:25:40,390 --> 01:25:42,059
Enter.

907
01:25:43,685 --> 01:25:48,982
We estimate...
250,000 dead on impact...

908
01:25:49,024 --> 01:25:51,818
and another quarter-million
projected within the year.

909
01:25:56,782 --> 01:25:57,824
Enter.

910
01:25:59,034 --> 01:26:01,828
Come on. Just push "enter,"
and it's done.

911
01:26:04,998 --> 01:26:07,167
Which is it going to be, hmm?

912
01:26:10,587 --> 01:26:12,548
Ahh. Hmm.

913
01:26:13,966 --> 01:26:17,511
To tell the truth, I thought
you were going to fold.

914
01:26:18,512 --> 01:26:20,430
Well, I'm dead either way.

915
01:26:21,390 --> 01:26:23,642
So do it yourself, asshole.

916
01:26:26,562 --> 01:26:27,938
Open the door!

917
01:26:33,193 --> 01:26:34,528
Night-night, honey.

918
01:27:19,323 --> 01:27:22,326
Cover me.
Good luck.

919
01:27:25,871 --> 01:27:27,748
Uhh! Uhh!

920
01:27:28,540 --> 01:27:29,791
Bring it in.

921
01:27:53,732 --> 01:27:55,317
Give me your hand.

922
01:28:08,080 --> 01:28:10,123
OK... you can come.

923
01:28:16,171 --> 01:28:17,881
Get me down there!

924
01:28:31,144 --> 01:28:32,729
Let's give those guys a haircut.

925
01:28:39,236 --> 01:28:40,445
Shit!

926
01:28:40,487 --> 01:28:41,655
Get down!

927
01:28:53,333 --> 01:28:54,459
Freeze!

928
01:29:23,113 --> 01:29:26,491
- Wow.
- That was a first for me, too.

929
01:30:05,030 --> 01:30:07,241
Uhh!

930
01:30:15,165 --> 01:30:16,708
Uhh!

931
01:30:36,520 --> 01:30:38,647
This is where
you two get off.

932
01:30:50,284 --> 01:30:51,285
No!

933
01:31:34,036 --> 01:31:36,246
- We're leaving, now!
- Yes, sir!

934
01:31:37,873 --> 01:31:39,625
- Where's Shepherd?
- He's supposed to be here.

935
01:31:39,666 --> 01:31:40,709
Find him!

936
01:31:57,142 --> 01:31:58,519
Cut the power!

937
01:32:00,729 --> 01:32:04,775
Aaah!

938
01:32:15,077 --> 01:32:16,662
Goddamn you, Hale.

939
01:32:22,417 --> 01:32:24,878
We're never going
to get clear in time.

940
01:32:24,920 --> 01:32:27,339
We need to shut down the nuke.
You hear me?

941
01:32:27,381 --> 01:32:30,342
- You need to disarm it.
- Find Hale.

942
01:32:55,826 --> 01:32:57,619
Oh, God. Your shoulder.

943
01:32:58,662 --> 01:33:01,915
- Help me off with this.
- Oh, God.

944
01:33:20,184 --> 01:33:23,687
No matter what, this train
can't make it to the city.

945
01:33:24,897 --> 01:33:27,232
So you stay here
and uncouple the car.

946
01:33:27,274 --> 01:33:28,859
I'm going to go after Deakins.

947
01:33:32,237 --> 01:33:34,698
- I'll see you soon.
- You promise?

948
01:33:53,091 --> 01:33:55,177
Fuck them if they
can't take a joke.

949
01:34:05,437 --> 01:34:07,064
What the fuck are you doing?

950
01:34:32,881 --> 01:34:35,092
Shut that son of a bitch
down, now!

951
01:34:35,092 --> 01:34:37,553
This ain't what I signed on for.

952
01:34:37,553 --> 01:34:39,972
I'm not ready to die,
not for you.

953
01:34:40,472 --> 01:34:44,309
Everybody dies, Kelly.
I'm as good a reason as any.

954
01:34:48,272 --> 01:34:50,691
Come on. Come on.

955
01:34:53,485 --> 01:34:54,528
Hale!

956
01:34:58,365 --> 01:34:59,867
Incoming!

957
01:35:01,702 --> 01:35:03,537
Uh!

958
01:35:05,163 --> 01:35:07,749
Yaaah!

959
01:35:28,478 --> 01:35:30,480
Come on out, Deak.
It's over.

960
01:35:46,330 --> 01:35:47,873
Ha ha ha!

961
01:35:52,211 --> 01:35:53,795
You lose.

962
01:35:53,837 --> 01:35:55,964
I still got my finger
on the trigger.

963
01:35:56,757 --> 01:35:58,592
That's the remote trigger.

964
01:35:58,634 --> 01:36:02,804
You see, if I press
this button here, you lose.

965
01:36:03,514 --> 01:36:05,474
And if I push this button...

966
01:36:06,767 --> 01:36:08,352
The weapon is disarmed.

967
01:36:09,770 --> 01:36:11,522
Why don't you disarm it, then?

968
01:36:12,356 --> 01:36:13,857
I'm not in the mood.

969
01:36:14,608 --> 01:36:16,068
Get rid of your weapon.

970
01:36:17,194 --> 01:36:18,737
Get rid of your weapon.

971
01:36:20,531 --> 01:36:21,823
Come on.

972
01:36:26,119 --> 01:36:28,580
That-a boy.
Now you can shut it down.

973
01:36:28,622 --> 01:36:30,958
You just have to
come and get it,

974
01:36:30,958 --> 01:36:34,127
and $20 that I took
from you last night...

975
01:36:35,420 --> 01:36:37,005
Says that you won't.

976
01:36:41,009 --> 01:36:44,513
- You're out of your mind.
- Yeah. Ain't it cool?

977
01:36:44,555 --> 01:36:48,058
I'm serious. Your mind
has taken a walk off the map.

978
01:36:48,058 --> 01:36:51,061
Maybe, but I'm still
going to kick your ass.

979
01:37:03,782 --> 01:37:05,909
All right,
you're bleeding, aren't you?

980
01:37:05,951 --> 01:37:09,538
Good. Let's see if we can't
get more out of you.

981
01:37:12,291 --> 01:37:13,375
Uh!

982
01:37:55,751 --> 01:37:57,753
Ahh!

983
01:38:02,299 --> 01:38:04,510
Every fight used to go
to a knockout.

984
01:38:04,551 --> 01:38:06,678
Know how it feels
to be knocked out?

985
01:38:26,698 --> 01:38:28,992
Your brain presses
against your skull,

986
01:38:29,034 --> 01:38:30,702
and it feels like this.

987
01:38:42,256 --> 01:38:43,715
Ah!

988
01:39:21,837 --> 01:39:23,422
Feel anything like that?

989
01:41:31,383 --> 01:41:32,551
I win.

990
01:41:33,427 --> 01:41:35,512
Sir, please turn around.

991
01:42:00,454 --> 01:42:02,331
My name is Riley Hale.

992
01:42:03,707 --> 01:42:05,209
Terry Carmichael.

993
01:42:06,335 --> 01:42:07,669
Pleased to meet you.

994
01:42:07,711 --> 01:42:10,589
You know, you're still
under arrest, captain.

995
01:42:10,631 --> 01:42:13,467
Oh, yeah?
I guess you better take me in.